Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.79,0:31:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as it occurs.\Nto be in a permanent state of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.64,0:32:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,surrenderingness.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.08,0:32:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a continuous process\Nwith no beginning and no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.96,0:32:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nyou allow that state to,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.15,0:32:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say, flow of its own. You\Nallow the state to flow of its own. I
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.36,0:32:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know what you're going to say\Nnext. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.20,0:32:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I don't have to uh demand that you tell\Nme what you're going to say next.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.64,0:32:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you say next is whatever you\Nsay next. And I have no
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.84,0:32:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uh position about it. So it's a it's\Nnon-positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.00,0:32:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-positionality.\N>> So I remember you said that just be the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.24,0:32:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,best of who you are. Is that pretty much\Nit?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.20,0:33:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She remembers she's saying\Nbe the best of uh you know uh try and do
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.24,0:33:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,your best the best that you can.\N>> That's all you can do. That's all you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.27,0:33:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can do. Be the best doggy you can be.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.24,0:33:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Give me your paw.\NThat's what I do. I give God my paw.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.27,0:33:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NNow it's up to God what he does with my
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.15,0:33:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,paw.\N>> Oink.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.12,0:33:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That is so cute. Thank you.\N>> Be a happy dog. Be a happy doggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.55,0:33:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> People say, "How do you reach
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.32,0:33:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment?" Just be a happy dog.\NJust keep wagging your tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.51,0:33:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Stop complaining and carrying on and\Nfussing. And
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.00,0:33:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I just try to keep my tail wagging, you\NOkay,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.76,0:33:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> that's all the I My dog wags her tail at\Nme in the morning and I wag my tail back
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.64,0:33:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're all happy. Everybody's happy.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.32,0:34:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you so much.\N>> Love all of life unconditionally in all
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.39,0:34:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of its expressions.\NSometimes the doggy's tail wags,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.36,0:34:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes it doesn't.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.39,0:34:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> thank you. You're welcome. You love\Neverything continuously no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.52,0:34:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, wait. This is hers.\N>> Very much. This is hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.91,0:34:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.11,0:34:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What daily prayers and practices would\Nbe useful for a spiritual student
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.15,0:34:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,seeking enlightenment?\N>> What what
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.11,0:34:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> what daily practices would be suitable\Nfor a student in daily practices? Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.52,0:34:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that's written extensively in the world\Nof literature. Are you really asking me
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.87,0:34:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the question?\NDid you ever hear meditation?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.76,0:34:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello.\N>> Okay. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.67,0:34:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What's he asking me?\N>> Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.07,0:35:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What is your question again?\N>> What daily prayers and practices would
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.07,0:35:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,be useful for\N>> daily prayers and practices? Okay. So
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.35,0:35:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation is the practice and prayers\Nare
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.44,0:35:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,prayers of thanks\Nuh requests divine requests of God. Dear
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.92,0:35:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,dear God please help me put my socks on\Nthe right feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.80,0:35:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for? the big\Npayoff. You know the magic prayer that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.83,0:35:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly you're enlightened. You know\Nwhat happens when you're enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.32,0:35:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't care about being enlightened.\NThe only people who care about being
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.83,0:35:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened are people who are not\Nenlightened. Once you're enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.28,0:35:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn't care less. The world would\Ncall it whatever calls it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.68,0:36:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not careful, they'll put you\Nin a, you know, funny house.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Can we get a picture?\N>> Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.52,0:36:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> They put you in the funny farm.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.20,0:36:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Wait, who wants a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.68,0:36:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh,\N>> I just wanted to thank you for the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.11,0:36:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,difference uh you've made in my life as\Nwell as my brothers and my mom. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.32,0:36:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you.\N>> Thank you for Kelly thanking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.72,0:36:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N>> Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.28,0:36:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The question is, is somebody enlightened\Nor are they
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.44,0:37:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We're politically correct today.\N>> Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.92,0:37:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> Love you, Dr. Hawkins. Love you, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.32,0:37:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.\N>> I have a question from the book I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.72,0:37:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and wanted to read two sentences and\Nthen ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.76,0:37:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right.\N>> Question.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.04,0:37:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One can view the spiritual ego as the\Ncurrent manifestation of one's karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.76,0:37:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that undoing the ego is the same as\Nresolving one's karma because they are
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.48,0:37:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,operationally one and the same.\NIf the term karma is not acceptable, one
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.28,0:37:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can use the term unconscious instead.\NSo my question is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.32,0:37:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,how is undoing the ego\Nand karma operationally
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.24,0:38:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the same?\NThe ego is karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.07,0:38:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is is a karmic creation.\NAnd then
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.07,0:38:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,one's inner attitude towards that ego\Nis one's uh spiritual state.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.16,0:38:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to take it seriously? Are\Nyou going to throw yourself down a well
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.76,0:38:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because your ego is condemning you?\NSo the inner attitude is one of uh
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.16,0:38:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh humility\Nand uh surrender without identifying
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.88,0:38:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with it.\NThe human condition is you see what it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.32,0:38:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is and the human brain operates in its\Nown way because that's our karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.64,0:38:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,inheritance as human beings.\NSo I always respect if God's will is for
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.00,0:39:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,me to have a brain that functions that\Nway, who am I to tell God that he's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.52,0:39:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong,\Nright? So you accept with humility the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.11,0:39:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,human condition. The human condition,\Nyou don't have to make it person. You
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.48,0:39:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to personalize it.\NYou can just accept it's the human
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.72,0:39:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,condition. You have two legs and two\Narms.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.88,0:39:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you don't have five? How come\Nyou don't have one? You know what I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.76,0:39:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,saying? So, it's dumb to keep asking\Nquestions about why is everything the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.04,0:39:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,way it is? It's obvious that it's God's\Nwill that it be that way. Yes. You just
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.80,0:39:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender it to\Nthe creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.28,0:39:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.\N>> God was bored, so he created human
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.96,0:39:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,beings.\NHe's regretted it ever since. But
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.20,0:39:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N>> You never never get a good night's rest
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.83,0:40:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore since I created humankind.\NThere's always some prayer bouncing off
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.07,0:40:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the floor of heaven. And\N>> pay attention to me. Pay attention to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.64,0:40:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,me. Oh,\N>> hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.72,0:40:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. I just like to uh I'm just here to\Nthank you for taking a machete to my
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.83,0:40:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.40,0:40:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Sometimes we drowned it too. Sometimes\N>> Sometimes we drowned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.24,0:40:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Sometimes we use a machete. Other times\Nwe just drowned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.20,0:40:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Even drowned it in pea soup.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.68,0:40:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.83,0:40:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I um I wanted to come actually offering\Nbringing something to you to both of you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.00,0:41:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to thank you but um and I was praying\Nand asked God to show me and uh nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.88,0:41:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,came and I just wanted to offer my\Nheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.68,0:41:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> And um just we'll cut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.59,0:41:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's the old Aztec technique. Cut your\Nheart right out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.72,0:41:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,pull it up for the crowd while it's\Nstill beating.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.07,0:41:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um I would really um I'm in 12step\Nrecovery. Been for a few years
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.00,0:41:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> in 12step recovery.\N>> And oh yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.16,0:41:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I just wanted to My first sponsor said\Nthat um AA can open the gates of hell
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.24,0:41:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and let you out. And um last night as I\Nwas uh falling asleep, that's a vision
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.92,0:41:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of you and it was you at the gates of\Nheaven um pushing them wide open and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.28,0:41:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with your arms open saying um you know\Nit's safe to surrender. Come on in. You
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.31,0:41:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,know it's your home too. And um\Njust want to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.11,0:41:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, it is God's gift to\Nuh the wretched.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.92,0:42:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, that's me.\NUm my question is um I've done what you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.96,0:42:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,said to do and dedicate my life to serve\Nyou know God self and others and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.35,0:42:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,recently I've got an opportunity an\Ninvitation to go stay at Ramana
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.76,0:42:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Maharashi's Ashram for an indefinite\Nperiod and also an invitation to come
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.40,0:42:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,serve with the missionaries of charity.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.64,0:42:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> yes\N>> and I wanted to see if you could ask the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.88,0:42:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,um ask the arm if that's in the highest\Ngood.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.28,0:42:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes, that's in the highest good.\N>> It's a pretty safe bet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.96,0:42:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\NUm,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.80,0:42:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess there are some dumb questions,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.80,0:42:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No, no, it's fine.\N>> That is a dumb question. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.48,0:42:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um,\N>> yes. It was mentioned earlier. I'll make
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.83,0:42:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this real quick. um in as you advance\Nand you get to those doorways um that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.11,0:43:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,those who have been there will you the\Nawareness of them having been there and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.96,0:43:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,who went through and who didn't\N>> will be there in the meditation reason
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.44,0:43:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had some very very seem to be high\Nstates glimpses of that ultimate exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.80,0:43:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,like you describe\N>> is it possible I brought a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.68,0:43:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,dollars if it takes that for you to do\Nit but would you could I look in your
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.59,0:43:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes and um if you could reflect the\Nreality of what I am so that I know it's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.24,0:43:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,safe to surrender.\N>> What is he requesting? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.04,0:43:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> He He just wants me to look at him and\Ntransmit to him that it's okay uh to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.31,0:43:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender. And\N>> cuz that terror comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.11,0:43:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> because the terror comes up every time\Nhe tries to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.07,0:43:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, well then you won't be able to make\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.48,0:43:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You either surrender to the terror and\Nstop trying to avoid it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.92,0:44:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or you don't.\NWhen you let go of the self as you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.28,0:44:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,understand it, you feel you're letting\Ngo of life and you feel a terror like
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.64,0:44:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for you are perhaps dying\Nto get through there. You just keep
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.24,0:44:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendering to that.\NEventually, it dies away
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.92,0:44:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're either alive or dead.\NOkay? You may live through it and maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.24,0:44:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not.\N>> Maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.11,0:44:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Since this is the last, maybe the last I\Ndon't know, you know, time I'll be this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.80,0:44:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,close to you in the physicality. I'm\Ntrying to let go of the attachment to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.92,0:44:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you. I'm in the process. Could I get a\Npicture to take with me to India,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.52,0:44:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,please? I got, like I said, got a couple\Ndollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.31,0:44:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What does he want?\N>> A picture to take with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.68,0:44:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To take with him more to heaven.\N>> To India.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.40,0:44:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> India.\N>> Yeah, that's where I'm going. Seems like
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.28,0:45:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the ashram. Raman Ashram.\N>> Oh yeah. You're going to India?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.59,0:45:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Like this is a huge deal. You\Nknow, it's a huge deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.52,0:45:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, um I feel safe. I just wanted\N>> to, you know. No, that sounds exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.16,0:45:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Yeah.\N>> Yeah. Just watch drinking the water
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.20,0:45:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\N>> Get all your shots.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.28,0:45:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, I'm Yeah. Somebody gave me a little\Nbottle of the water from the Ganges
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.24,0:45:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,recently.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And it came back from India and we\Ncalibrated it. It was 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.72,0:45:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Right.\N>> So, be sure and have a swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.76,0:45:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,while you're there.\N>> Okay. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.35,0:45:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> Thank you. We don't need that.
